item.description: Biography I’m currently a PhD candidate in Economics at Indiana University. Below you can find my notes and what I’m working on. I’m interested in empirical Economics and data visualization. I enjoy using data to help shed new light on problems. I’m particularly interested in how data can help improve healthcare policy. When I’m not working I love to play softball or soccer. Or take a ride on my motorcycle around Monroe County.

item.title: What I'm reading
item.description: I love to read in my spare time. Here are some of the books I’m reading right now: The Elements of Statistical Learning Measure for Measure The Color of Law The Great Poems of the Bible
